What go mod tidy will do?

    Resolved the Dependency Graph: It looked at your imports in main.go and your controllers and figured out exactly which versions of the Kubernetes API (client-go, apimachinery) are compatible with each other.

    Populated go.sum: This file is now filled with cryptographic hashes. It ensures that every time you (or your viewers) build this project, you are using the exact same code, preventing "dependency hijacking."

    Local Caching: All those K8s libraries are now stored in your $GOPATH/pkg/mod. This means you can now compile your operator offline or without waiting for slow downloads again.
